A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Consumer Protection – Automatic Tip Prompt Screen – Requirements
3 FOR the purpose of requiring certain businesses that use a point–of–sale system that
4 automatically prompts a customer to leave a tip to disclose to whom the tip will be
5 allocated and display a tip amount that is set at zero by default; establishing that a
6 violation of this Act is an unfair, abusive, or deceptive trade practice; and generally
7 relating to automatic tip prompt screen requirements.
